Still a bit of a work in progress, but I have had success simulating the slash with the following style (and by adding the class `fa-slash` to items that want a slash):

```
i.fa.fa-slash::after {
  content: '\2571';
  font-weight: bold;
  text-shadow: 0.75px 0px 0px white;
  position: absolute;
  left: 1px;
  transform: scale(3,0.7) translate(0.5px, 1px) skewX(41deg);
}
```

I call it a work in progress because it requires tweaking the `transform` parameters to position and size the slash to accommodate various FontAwesome characters.

As a preview, the style above almost exactly emulates the slash on fa-eye:

